        </title>
        <caption>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='12'>📄 High Priority States</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='12'>Purpose</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='12'>Highlights states classified as High Priority to focus attention on jurisdictions with the highest normalized reporting rates.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='12'>Methodology</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='12'>States are filtered using the Priority Level calculated in the SQL view. Rankings are based on the normalized reporting rate rather than raw allegation totals.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='12'>Key Insight</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Tableau Light' fontsize='12'>This view narrows the analysis to jurisdictions that may warrant additional investigation. The priority classification is intended as a decision-support indicator and should always be interpreted alongside local reporting practices.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </caption>
